<subSubSection id="F1F9AEBB9C5B2A14EF91584CFD265C8D" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5B2A14EF91584CFEF25DD8" blockId="35.[151,1437,1504,2036]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5B2A11EF91584CFDB15BAC" bold="true" box="[199,567,1648,1676]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Description of 3 
<superScript id="4E9650789C5B2A11EEDF584FFE1E5B5E" attach="left" box="[393,408,1648,1662]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">rd</superScript>
instar larva.
</emphasis>
Size (based on 
<specimenCount id="AFE536B99C5B2A11EDA7584CFC055BAC" box="[753,899,1651,1676]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="generic">7 specimens</specimenCount>
): BL 
<quantity id="7E1B50D59C5B2A11EC93584CFBA85BAA" box="[965,1070,1651,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.48" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="9.48">9.48 mm</quantity>
; HL 
<quantity id="7E1B50D59C5B2A11EB3D584CFB575BAA" box="[1131,1233,1651,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.27" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.27">2.27 mm</quantity>
(2.15–2.49), HW 
<quantity id="7E1B50D59C5B2A11EFC158A9FF7B5B8E" box="[151,253,1686,1711]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.86" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.86">1.86 mm</quantity>
(1.71–1.96), ML 
<quantity id="7E1B50D59C5B2A11EE9D58A9FDB75B8E" box="[459,561,1686,1711]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.98" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.98">1.98 mm</quantity>
(1.90–2.22), HW/HL 0.74, ML/HL 0.92. General colouring ochre with pink shades and mottled with dark brown, ventral side very pale with dark markings; head capsule with dark occipital markings, lateral sides with dark markings, ocular tubercles black, ventral side of the head pale except the gular area; mandibles orange; legs pale; setae mostly black except some white bristles in anterior portion of the body. Head longer than wide; anterior margin of the labrum covered by white dolichasters (
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EB035919FB305A1F" box="[1109,1206,1830,1855]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[218,1356,205,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-43@37.[206,1365,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Megistopus lucasi (Navás, 1912), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Chia). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909431/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
); mandibles slender, slightly shorter than the head capsule (
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11ED1A5974FD2A5A44" box="[588,684,1867,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[218,1356,205,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-43@37.[206,1365,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Megistopus lucasi (Navás, 1912), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Chia). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909431/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 19a</figureCitation>
), distance between the base of the mandible and basal tooth larger than that between the basal and apical teeth; interdental mandibular setae: (2)(1)(1)(0); labial palpi covered by whitish dolichasters (
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EEDF59ACFE6A5A8C" box="[393,492,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[218,1356,205,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-43@37.[206,1365,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Megistopus lucasi (Navás, 1912), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Chia). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909431/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 19e</figureCitation>
). Pronotum covered by sparse setae, anterior setae paler in colour (
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EBA759ACFAD25A8C" box="[1265,1364,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[241,1323,508,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-216@11.[233,1335,499,1910]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pronotum of 3rd instar larvae of Dendroleontini and Nemoleontini; A, Dendroleon pantherinus; B, Nemoleon notatus; C, Distoleon tetragrammicus; D, Creoleon lugdunensis; E, Neuroleon nemausiensis; F, Macronemurus appendiculatus; G, Megistopus lucasi; H, Gymnocnemia variegata. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909373/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 4G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EA3759ACFA085A8C" box="[1377,1422,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[218,1356,205,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-43@37.[206,1365,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Megistopus lucasi (Navás, 1912), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Chia). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909431/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">19b</figureCitation>
); mesothoracic spiracles cylindrical, raised on tubercle but comparatively stout, shorter than the first pair of setiferous processes (
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EED359E4FE615AD4" box="[389,487,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[218,1356,205,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-43@37.[206,1365,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Megistopus lucasi (Navás, 1912), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Chia). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909431/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 19d</figureCitation>
); mesothoracic setiferous processes pedunculated. Abdominal spiracles slightly protruding, not visible from above; VIII sternite without odontoid processes; IX sternite with a pair of dark markings on the side; rastra short and equipped with 4 digging setae, internal seta less than a quarter of the others in size (
